cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method for defining an ordered domain for information on the web, making it comparable and searchable. This falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The use of distance functions and metric spaces also suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of words and numbers for representing domain vectors suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL).
